    Using Gemsets
  %hr

%p
  To use a gem set
%pre.code
  :preserve
    ∴ rvm gems albinochipmunk
%p
  This will create the gemset if it does not exist.

%p
  Alternatively we can switch to a gemset when we use a ruby by appending %gemsetname to the end of the ruby selector string:
%pre.code
  :preserve
    ∴ rvm use 1.9.1%albinochipmunk

%p
  To use a named gem set with an rvm 'do' action, append it to the ruby selector string using a '%'
%pre.code
  :preserve
    rvm 1.9.1%albinochipmunk,ree%albinochipmunk,jruby%albinochipmunk rake test


%p
  If you are aware of where you are at and wish to fix the gemset you can do:
%pre.code
  :preserve
    rvm gems albinochipmunk
    rvm 1.9.1,ree,jrubyrake --sticky_gems test

